A vain, self-righteous nobleman falls in love with a village girl and tries to transform her into his version of the ideal woman.
Follow the lives, loves, highs and lows of four members of the Women's Land Army who are working at the Hoxley Estate during WWII.
After seducing a philandering con man, a rebellious young woman enlists his help in carrying out a heinous crime against her sister.
An ex-CIA contractor turned thief is forced to head a CIA gambit to infiltrate a black ops Mexican prison and steal $50 million in drug cartel money.

title_name: Larry Charles' Dangerous World of Comedy
description: Legendary comedy writer and director Larry Charles travels the world in search of humor in the most unusual, unexpected and dangerous places.
Two curious worms spend their days investigating the otherworldly objects that fall through the grate into their subterranean world.
Stranded on a tropical island, two silly larva buddies find slapstick fun in everything from discovering food to meeting new animal friends.
Based on the book "Las Fantásticas," this exciting telenovela follows the tumultuous lives of five women who get mixed up with the Mafia.
A commercial diver becomes trapped on the ocean floor with dwindling oxygen and little hope of a timely rescue, so he tries to save himself.
In a docuseries set at one of NCAA football's most fertile recruiting grounds, guys with red flags seek to prove their worth on the field and in class.
Seeking romance and friendship, a young gay lawyer travels to Fire Island in the off-season and is soon on the run after witnessing a murder.
When disaster strikes mid-flight, a commercial plane's frantic passengers confront their pasts and the possibility of death. Based on true events.
After causing the near extinction of mankind seven years ago, genius scientist Leon Lau must now fight the ecological disaster he unwittingly created.
Two widowed childhood sweethearts fall for each other all over again when they are reunited over the Internet after nearly 60 years.

title_name: Late Life: The Chien-Ming Wang Story
description: Injuries sidelined the bright career of New York Yankees pitcher Chien-Ming Wang. This documentary captures his relentless battle back to the majors.

title_name: Lavell Crawford: Can a Brother Get Some Love?
description: "Last Comic Standing" runner-up Lavell Crawford lords over a hometown crowd at St. Louis's Orpheum Theatre, raking in the love – and the laughs.
Before one of them moves to the U.S., two childhood friends promise to reunite as adults. But illness and the vagaries of the heart stand in the way.
After discovering old fractures in her skull, a photographer recovering from amnesia becomes increasingly haunted by a sinister childhood secret.
This true-to-life action saga profiles Virginia's bootlegging Bondurant brothers, whose exploits during the Prohibition era made them outlaw heroes.
Four couples – a speed-dating pair, a husband and wife, a man living with an older woman and co-workers with opposite views – weather ups and downs.
In response to the repeated bigotry she faces, a Muslim teen in Amsterdam tries to find a sense of belonging in the world of fundamentalist Islam.
This documentary retraces the footsteps of Adolf Hitler's mysterious nephew and explores what became of the Hitler family line.
Félicie and Victor, two young friends in 1880s France, escape from an orphanage to pursue their dreams in Paris, the glittering City of Lights.
Best friends Léa and Camille explore the notion of healing while traveling to Latin America in search of a cure for a terminal disease.

In this entertaining installment of the wildly popular early-learning series, Professor Quigley, Leap, Lily and Tad arrive at the magical Letter Factory, where jumbles of sounds are miraculously shaped into letters.
Fans, experts and creators of the "League of Legends" detail the game’s rise from free demo to global esports titan.
Scout takes a magical trip to a farm where an alligator and other friendly critters teach him all about sounding out the letters of the alphabet.
With transport support from their magic car, Axel, the LeapFrog pets make a new friend named Max, who helps them learn counting skills in Numberland.
Using rhythm and rhymes, a funky band and a colorful cast of characters help make reading, sounding out vowels and building words easy and fun!

title_name: Learning Songs by Little Baby Bum: Nursery Rhyme Friends
description: Simple songs mix with colorful animation to teach youngsters about concepts such as animals, vehicles, numbers, colors and more.
Colorful characters and edutaining activities help make learning English fun in this series geared toward youngsters.
The spirit of a murdered woman contacts four bachelors, enlisting their help to find her killer.
Born into a rare supernatural bloodline, Hope Mikaelson attends a gifted private school to master her powers and control her innate urges for evil.
Identical twins and notorious gangsters Reggie and Ronnie Kray elude the authorities in 1960s London while transfixing and terrifying the public.
When an evil force threatens his village, a gifted teen who can talk to ghosts puts his skills to good use, one legend at a time.
When mythical creatures come to life, it's up to Leo, Teodora, Don Andrés and Alebrije – super-secret monster hunters – to save the day.
Three assassins – magician Lei Ying, hit man Tieh Hon and kung fu master Ti Tan – are sent to Yunnan by their clan leader to bring to justice another clan member who betrayed the tribe.

title_name: LEGO Bionicle: The Journey to One
description: Six legendary heroes find themselves on an epic quest as they harness the power of nature's elements to defeat the forces of evil.
A trio of siblings gets trapped in a secret temple, where they must navigate a risky obstacle course to make it out. Inspired by the ‘90s game show.
When Superman and the other Justice League superheroes start disappearing, it's up to Batman to unravel the caper and save the day.
Armed with a powerful amulet, a teenage guardian is tasked with protecting her little sister – and all of Elvendale. Based on the popular web series.
As a way to make friends, new girl in town Olivia volunteers to work at the Heartlake City World Petacular with four other girls.

title_name: Lego Friends: Girls on a Mission
description: Five best friends put their teamwork, wits and courage to the test when they take on a mission to protect Heartlake City from bad people.

title_name: LEGO Friends: The Power of Friendship
description: Five best friends face adventures side by side in their hometown. Zany antics, love and missteps are better with friends!

title_name: LEGO House - Home of the Brick
description: In Billund, Denmark, a nearly 130,000-square-foot house is constructed with 25 million Lego bricks, capturing the awe of kids of all ages.

title_name: LEGO Jurassic World: The Indominus Escape
description: The scientists of Jurassic World create a captivating and terrifying new creature that loves hot dogs. But what happens when the hot dogs run out?

title_name: LEGO Marvel Super Heroes: Avengers Reassembled!
description: When Ultron seizes control of Iron Man's armor, the Avengers race to save their friend and stop an evil plot to take over the world.

title_name: LEGO Marvel Super Heroes: Black Panther
description: When Thanos joins forces with villains Killmonger and Klaue to destroy Earth, Black Panther rushes to stop them from stealing Wakanda's vibranium.

title_name: LEGO Marvel Super Heroes: Guardians of the Galaxy
description: The Guardians are on a mission to deliver the Build Stone to the Avengers before the Ravagers, Thanos and his underlings steal it from them.
Kai, Jay, Cole and Zane must master their elemental powers and Spinjitzu weapons to protect the land of Ninjago, which also has an underworld.

title_name: LEGO Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu: Day of the Departed
description: Cole finds himself trapped in Yang's temple after accidentally releasing a host of villainous spirits that the Ninja must defeat.

title_name: LEGO: Marvel Super Heroes: Maximum Overload
description: Villainous Loki is amassing an army to conquer Earth! His antics are keeping Spider-Man and S.H.I.E.L.D. busy as they tackle a host of bad guys.
In a near-future world where an oppressive regime segregates society, one woman skirts the system to search for the daughter taken from her years ago.
To upgrade his life, a simple man fakes his credentials as a lawyer when sudden extraordinary abilities give him the talent to thrive.

title_name: Lemony Snicket's A Series of Unfortunate Events
description: After their parents are tragically killed, three orphans are taken in by the dastardly Count Olaf, who hopes to snatch their inheritance from them.
Four doctors at New York's storied Lenox Hill Hospital balance their personal lives and their dedication to their patients in this documentary series.
Addicted to webcams and voyeurism, a married man gets more than he bargained for when an online stranger tries to force him to watch a suicide.
Spunky leopard cub Leo and his loyal tiger pal Tig team up for fun and adventure as they explore the forest and learn about ancient legends.

title_name: Lessons from a School Shooting: Notes from Dunblane
description: Two priests – one from Dunblane, Scotland, the other from Newtown, Connecticut – bond over school tragedies that occurred 16 years apart.
A snowstorm hits a small town on a cold Christmas Eve, affecting the friendships, love lives and futures of several high school seniors.
From trying to seduce Prince to battling sleep apnea, Leslie Jones traces her evolution as an adult in a joyfully raw and outrageous stand-up special.
This documentary chronicles simmering tension and broken trust between L.A.'s black community and police in the decade before the Rodney King riots.
Some returning combat veterans suffer scars that are more psychological than physical. This film follows patients and staff during their treatment.
After his crew breaks up, a gifted but insecure hip-hop dancer teaches at a top ballet school in Paris, where he falls for an aspiring ballerina.
Disillusioned with her humdrum routine, a married lawyer secretly enrolls in a dance school in this remake of the 1996 Japanese film “Shall We Dance?”
Two classmates from elementary school reunite as next-door neighbors and discover their relationship was – and still is – defined by food.
With the help of her neighbors, a divorced woman residing in a one-person-household apartment complex learns to balance living alone and eating well.
Young Levius rises through the ranks in the brutal world of metal boxing under his uncle's guidance. Forces outside the ring have their eye on him.
Destiny brings Mecnun and Leyla together as newborns, and again years later. Despite unexpected turns in Mecnun's zany life, Leyla remains a constant.
A young woman's attempt to come out of the closet on Thanksgiving gets complicated when her male roommate shows up to her parents' home unannounced.
A woman from a small mountain village disobeys her village elders and sets out for the big city in search of her missing husband.
When a shy teen transfers to a new school, he elects to mix things up by playing along with the rumor that he's a vampire.
Filmmakers explore how pop culture shapes a new generation's beliefs about gender, sexuality and violence on display among students on spring break.
An adventure-loving young woman catches the attention of a handsome beau in this musical celebration of love, friends and fate.
At Korea's top university medical center, ideals and interests collide between a patient-centered ER doctor and the hospital's newly-appointed CEO.
Computer users across the globe log onto the virtual world of Second Life. But some users' lives are dramatically consumed by this alternate reality.
Following the death of his beloved girlfriend, Beth, Zach is first shattered and then overjoyed when she inexplicably comes back to life.
Holly and Eric discover reciprocal hatred during their first date, but must put their feelings aside after becoming guardians of their friends' baby.
A group of Mumbai up-and-comers search for love and struggle for success in this ensemble drama that centers on an eager young call-center executive.
A couple operates a bustling dog rescue out of their own home, vowing to give a safe space to the neediest pups on the planet – 10,000 and counting.
A vengeful son, a cop on a mission, a wannabe actress and a jilted lover find their lives intermingling in unexpected ways over 24 hours in Mumbai.
When authorities jail his son for rejecting religious bias, a poor father’s struggle to bail him out highlights rural India’s enduring casteism.
In the grip of trauma, hundreds of refugee children in Sweden withdraw from life's uncertainties into a coma-like illness called Resignation Syndrome.
Two parallel life paths begin for a man and woman in love after she is offered a lucrative promotion far away and must choose between love and career.
Cured of what she thought was terminal cancer, Stella Abbott faces a slew of experiences – good and bad – resulting from years of "living for today."
Seeking job opportunities, a young man arrives in Cairo and becomes increasingly involved with the family of a wealthy businessman.
Johnnie To's character-centered drama follows a Hong Kong firefighting crew as they take on harrowing rescue missions and navigate personal dilemmas.
A terrifying home invasion shatters a couple's happy family life and brings their marriage to the brink as painful fallout unfolds.
Over 50 years of their lives, a couple enjoys the blessings and setbacks of parenting, and learns that God has to be at the center of their family.
After she's left at the altar, a workaholic advertising executive ends up on her Caribbean honeymoon cruise with her estranged father.
This intimate portrait depicts the rise of artist Lil Peep, whose genre-bending music attracted a massive following and ultimately defined his life.
After each of them loses a child to murder, two women who meet in a support group initiate their own investigation when the police are no help.
A woman who's about to give birth finds her maternal instincts kicking in when she's abducted, imprisoned and brutalized by a vicious gang.
After testifying against the Mafia, ex-gangster Frank Tagliano enters witness protection and asks to be sent to Norway.
This documentary follows eight women in India who struggle with self-confidence and society's expectations but rediscover themselves through running.
Scottish comic Brian "Limmy" Limond headlines this sketch series featuring him in various roles from a TV psychic to costumed adventurer "Falconhoof."
A Hong Kong intelligence officer tasked with finding undercover agents whose identities have been erased finds herself in the paths of rival triads.
Kidnapped as a child and raised in the circus, a young lion tamer’s tough side emerges when he gets entangled in an underworld murder mystery.
When her father falls ill, Adaeze steps up to run the family business – alongside her uncle – and prove herself in a male-dominated world.
After crossing paths at a crime scene, a renowned math teacher and an antiques appraiser embark on an unexpected journey of love and self-discovery.
A pregnant Liss Pereira shares hilariously uncomfortable truths about sex, love, attraction and the lies we tell in modern relationships.
This compilation for preschoolers features a peppy young bus and his first life experiences where bumps in the road won't stop him from a fun ride.

title_name: Little Baby Bum: Nursery Rhyme Friends
description: Twinkle, Mia, Jacus and the rest of the Nursery Rhyme Friends perform catchy tunes for the little ones.
Seeking to improve his combat skills, a young man falls in love with a woman with mystical powers, but his past stands in the way of their union.
After moving from New York City to a small town in Washington state, an interracial couple and their preteen son struggle to adjust to their new life.
In this horror-comedy, a recently married man who wants to bond with his stepson begins to fear that the boy is a demon.
In an ancient sport traditionally reserved for men, 20-year-old female sumo prodigy Hiyori attempts to revolutionize Japan’s national pastime.
A spinoff of Rohit Shetty's action franchise, this animated series follows brave kid cop Little Singham’s adventures as he defends his town from evil.

title_name: Little Singham aur Kaal ka Mahajaal
description: When Kaal, the vilest demon on earth, threatens to destroy his village, child cop Little Singham must use his strength and smarts to fight back.

title_name: Little Singham Bandarpur Mein Hu Ha Hu
description: Little Singham's sidekick monkey, Chikki, is stuck in the magical land of Bandarpur! Can the kid cop save his beloved pet before danger strikes?
Little Singham is in London to meet the queen, but when the famed Kohinoor Diamond gets stolen, the kid cop goes on a wild, citywide hunt for the thief.
Kaal is back – bigger and badder than ever! Can Little Singham fight the battle of a lifetime to stop the demon’s plans to wreak havoc on earth?
As fears rise over a ghost known for nighttime abductions, Mirchi Nagar residents look to the only person they know can save them: Little Singham!
In a journey back in time to the ancient city of Mirchigadh, Little Singham vies for the title of Ultimate Warrior and fights a zombie king’s army.
A cohabiting couple in their 20s navigate the ups and downs of work, modern-day relationships and finding themselves in contemporary Mumbai.
Akko enrolls at the Luna Nova Witchcraft Academy. She's not the best student, but her bright attitude is the key to her and her friends' success.

title_name: Littlest Pet Shop: A World of Our Own
description: In Paw-Tucket, pets of all types form friendships, pursue their passions and have a great time being themselves.
After four years in Hollywood as a television star, Liv returns to Wisconsin to discover that either she – or her family – has changed.
The police officers at South Korea's busiest patrol division toil day and night as keepers of law and peace – but the reality is far from orderly.
When Emilio (Oscar Martínez) is diagnosed with Alzheimer's disease, he and his family embark on a quest to reunite him with his childhood crush.
Pushed together by twists of time, a Joseon doctor and a cardiac surgeon overcome their 400-year divide as they learn and heal through each other.
Mentored by an enigmatic tycoon, an ambitious young man faces a crisis when his rise in power draws him deep into the occult.
Eight undocumented families' fates roller-coast as the United States' immigration policies are transformed.
Burned out on life, Miles undergoes a strange procedure at a strip mall spa – and wakes to find he's been replaced by a better version of himself.
Beloved children's book character Llama Llama springs to life in this heartwarming series about family, friendship and learning new things.

title_name: Lo más sencillo es complicarlo todo
description: When a 17-year-old learns the TV news host she pines for is engaged, she and her best friend launch an elaborate plan to prevent his marriage.
A disillusioned rickshaw driver in Punjab dreams of moving to Dubai, but his plan to butter up his would-be benefactor goes horribly wrong.
Four friends become overnight millionaires after selling their video game start-up. But their newfound status tests their friendship and resolve.
A widower believes he must marry off his three problematic daughters before he can pursue his real goal of marrying his secret love.
After their dad's murder, three siblings move with their mom to his ancestral estate, where they discover magical keys that unlock powers — and secrets.
When his chatty nature lands him in trouble, an unlucky meatball seller flees Istanbul and finds a new life on a beautiful island.
Manipulated into embezzling funds for her boyfriend and sentenced to prison, a naïve young woman must quickly learn to survive in a harsh new world.
A government agent wrongly accused of a crime gets a shot at freedom if he can engineer a high-risk rescue mission to outer space.
A young man and woman fall in love but are threatened to be torn apart by the tensions between their Latino and Caucasian communities in Arizona.
A torrid affair between a passionate lowborn poet and a wealthy Moscow heiress is engulfed by class difference, criminality and, eventually, murder.
Lives are upended when a hiking trip leads a Wall Street hotshot to explore his true feelings for an old pal who’s disenchanted with his boyfriend.
An elderly woman finds her life disrupted when her family and village realize she has a chance at a world record for being the oldest grandmother alive.
After finding love in drug-free Dubai, Stefan returns to Germany to grab documents for his wedding. But old buddy Kai's bad habits complicate things.
When his reclusive-banker lover disappears, a hard-partying young British hedonist plunges into the dangerous world of espionage to find the truth.
When Juan Catalan is arrested for a murder he didn't commit, he builds his case for innocence around raw footage from a popular TV show. A documentary.
This documentary follows the 2016 tour of beloved rock band The Tragically Hip as they make their way across Canada one last time.
This contemporary crime thriller focuses on a Wyoming sheriff who's rebuilding his life and career following the death of his wife.

title_name: Loo Loo Kids: Johny & Friends Musical Adventures
description: Music-loving baby Johny goes on dance-filled adventures with his family, friends and adorable critters in this colorful, animated preschooler series.
While keeping his identity secret, a real estate billionaire tries to woo an outspoken croupier who talks gamblers out of losing their money.
An officer killed on the job returns to Earth as a ghost to solve his own murder and seek justice with the help of a rookie cop and some funky magic.
Under a government initiative, a retired alcoholic soccer player is sent to establish a soccer team in a politically troubled area.
Lorena Ramírez of Mexico's Rarámuri community lives a pastoral life – except when she straps on her sandals to compete as an ultramarathon runner.
Spurred by boredom and peer pressure, a group of suburban teens becomes increasingly violent and find their paths intersecting those of their parents.
This documentary pays tribute to the young cadets who gave their lives to defend Mexico against U.S. forces during the battle of Chapultepec Castle.
Featuring never-before-seen images, personal testimonies and more, this is the story of one of the most notorious drug smugglers of all time.

title_name: Los Tigres del Norte at Folsom Prison
description: The beloved norteño band Los Tigres del Norte performs for the inmates of Folsom Prison on the 50th anniversary of Johnny Cash's iconic concert.
In a "winning is everything" society, how do we handle failure? This series profiles athletes who have turned the agony of defeat into human triumph.
Teen singers-songwriters in an elite music program form bonds of friendship, creativity and romance while turning their passion into their profession.
Facing a murder charge, a genius mechanic with a criminal past must track down a missing car containing the proof of his innocence: a single bullet.
Desperate to find her missing daughter, a mother fights to uncover the truth — and helps expose a string of unsolved murders. Based on a true story.
Nigerian students Okon and Bona experience culture shock – several shocks, really – after being selected for an exchange program in London.
After crash-landing on an alien planet, the Robinson family fights against all odds to survive and escape. But they're surrounded by hidden dangers.
Grammy-winning singer Loudon Wainwright III reflects upon his unique relationship with his father in an evening of original songs and heartfelt stories.
War looms over the kingdom of Neunatia, where two young women are both burdened and blessed by the power of song.
A man in an unsatisfying marriage recalls the details of an intense past relationship with an ex-girlfriend when he gets word that she may be missing.
Rebellious Mickey and good-natured Gus navigate the thrills and agonies of modern relationships in this bold comedy co-created by Judd Apatow.
In Jakarta, five couples of varying ages and backgrounds experience the different stages of romantic love, from its giddy start to its painful end.
Radically changed by a misunderstanding 13 years ago, a biotech expert runs into an old flame and suffers an illness that takes her back to the past.
While trying to make their teacher fall for a basketball coach, four misfits and a model student find friendship, love and the courage to be themselves.
When professional ambitions clash with personal feelings for a modern-day couple, a love story from a bygone decade may offer some wisdom.
Frustrated by life with her boyfriend, thirty-something Wako can’t stop herself from being interested in high schooler Yumeaki, despite their age gap.
In a world where an app alerts people if someone in the vicinity likes them, Kim Jojo experiences young love while coping with personal adversities.
The lives of five strangers become intertwined forever when a starlet filming a documentary is kidnapped on the streets of Hong Kong.
A sexually inexperienced rickshaw driver struggles to build intimacy with his shy new wife in their tiny, overcrowded quarters.
After a chance meeting at a ballpark, the kind son of a former gangster tries to help an outgoing radio DJ get over her recent heartbreak.
After enrolling in a college poetry course, a struggling rapper finds inspiration for her new voice through slam poetry.
Three years after making a wild promise to a woman in distress, a rigid businessman runs into her again and must decide whether to honor his word.
A successful Taiwanese chef moves home from Europe to teach at a cooking school. He soon clashes with a pretty teacher he met under odd circumstances.

title_name: Love Dot Com: The Social Experiment
description: Sparks fly and romance blooms when Shelby, a vegan chef, meets Greg, a developer – until their opposing views clash.
A wealthy heir's search for a nameless childhood sweetheart leads him to an inn run by a family with three sisters. But which one is his true love?
Richard accepts a bet that he can't find a companion to a friend's wedding, not knowing the dating app he's using includes a 45-day contract.
Exhausted with his mother’s failed attempts at setting him up with women, Ican hires an ideal partner from a matchmaking app.

title_name: Love for Ten: Generation of Youth
description: A nerdy engineering student falls for a pretty, outgoing girl at his college. To get closer to her, he joins the theater group she belongs to.

When the Hong Kong government enacts a ban on smoking cigarettes indoors, the new law drives hard-core smokers outside, facilitating a meeting between Cherie, a makeup saleswoman, and Jimmy, an advertising exec.
Two young artists, a violin player and an actress, fight to achieve their dreams and keep their relationship together during Christmastime.
Diagnosed with selective perception, a young woman is prescribed by a psychotherapist to spend time with a troubled man she cannot see.
Nick and Vanessa Lachey host this social experiment where single men and women look for love and get engaged, all before meeting in person.
Toprak, who lost her baby, is hired as a wet nurse for wealthy Yusuf's motherless son. Yusuf is drawn to Toprak, but also to her scheming sister.
An adoring couple elects to test the strength of their marriage when they run against each other for the office of state governor.
To assert her independence from her rigid father’s expectations, a headstrong woman hires a desperate Los Angeles man to pose as her fiancé in Africa.
After wealthy college boy Ömer and lower class college girl Aysem fall in love and quickly marry, they learn that love and life aren't always perfect.
When a marriage-phobic woman hires a seductress to test how faithful her eager-to-wed boyfriend is, her plan takes an unexpected turn.
Not romantically inclined, a popular radio personality finds herself caught between two diametrically opposed suitors.
When her loved ones cook up a morbid plan to make her take time off from work, Yang Yiru goes on a vacation, truly believing she has terminal cancer.
When a computer-science major gets dumped by her “husband” in an online role-playing game, she attracts a new proposal from the game’s top player.
A college stud tries to level up his relationship with a computer science major after becoming attracted to her skills in an online role-playing game.
Cherie and Jimmy's relationship is in a rut – until Cherie's estranged father shows up and a woman from Jimmy's past shows up with a hidden agenda.
To prove himself to a love interest, a delivery boy learns dubious kung fu from an aging charlatan so he can challenge his archrival to a fight.
Individually, bank employees Sanjay and Karina don't earn enough to be able to buy a home, so they decide to enter into a marriage of convenience.
A successful DJ's bachelor lifestyle is upended by a young woman who claims to be his long lost daughter.
Single coworkers at a radio station are brought together by mutual friends, but their starry-eyed notions about love may scuttle their romance.
Three grown siblings must rethink their idea of family when they learn their parents are getting divorced and have their eyes on new partners.
Different versions of the same day unfold as Jack juggles difficult guests, unbridled chaos and potential romance at his sister's wedding.
A love triangle gets complicated when a female English tutor unknowingly gets between a hot-tempered guy and his off-to-the-United States girlfriend.
High schooler Yuta wants to leave his past as a delusional weirdo behind. But his classmate Rikka has her own delusions, and she's interested in his.
Terrifying creatures, wicked surprises and dark comedy converge in this NSFW anthology of animated stories presented by Tim Miller and David Fincher.
When a fashion blogger falls for a video game vlogger, their romance goes viral. But separating their virtual life from reality gets complicated.
When a group of people meets at the same party, they form four different relationships, each experiencing similar phases of love.
In his quest for true love, Dylan found chlamydia. Joined by friends Evie and Luke, he relives past encounters as he notifies all his former partners.
Love and academics get complicated at an all-male college that happens to be located next to an all-female high school.
Best friends Sarah and Mindy share an unexpected moment while on a road trip. Years later, the two struggle to reconnect before a wedding.
When a newly single photographer is forced to work with a longtime rival, the battle of their egos turns into a chance for love.
Struggling in a loveless marriage, a hard-drinking, workaholic cop finds a chance at redemption after a fateful incident leaves him wounded.
This provocative drama examines how the voyeuristic nature of modern society affects three unusual couples in Northern India.
Middle schooler Kai's depressing life in a boring fishing village changes drastically when a local mermaid named Lu joins his band.
Deadpan twin comics Keith and Kenny Lucas take the stage in Brooklyn with a set that touches on drugs, race, Deion Sanders, teachers and O.J. Simpson.

title_name: Luccas Neto em: Acampamento de Férias 2
description: Luccas and his band of buddies make music and mischief at a new summer camp, where they face off with talented rivals and their tough coach.
When Luccas Neto plans a big Children's Day celebration, an unexpected threat at school puts the party – and his friends – at risk.
Luccas and Gi are heading to a world famous gymkhana camp. Only problem: so are their bullies... A fun musical that will get you in a vacation mood.

title_name: Luccas Neto in: The End of Christmas
description: To save Christmas, Luccas and Gi head to the North Pole and are recruited by Santa Claus to find all the gifts that have mysteriously disappeared.
Known simply as "Lucha," field hockey player Luciana Aymar shares her tumultuous and triumphant journey to become the best in the world.
Argentina's Luciano Mellera emphasizes the humorous and fantastical aspects of childhood through comedic impersonations and insights on daily life.
After searching for his abducted son for three years, a devastated father attempts to track down his missing child through lucid dreams.
Bored with being the Lord of Hell, the devil relocates to Los Angeles, where he opens a nightclub and forms a connection with a homicide detective.
When Vikram gets tapped to play the male lead in a Bollywood film, he can't believe his luck. But it may ruin his relationship with his girlfriend.
When his friends make a bet that he can woo his college crush, a lovesick student named Luckee struggles between satisfying his heart and hormones.
After being arrested for a crime he didn't commit, an aspiring musician teams up with some of his inmates at Lucknow Central to form a band.
When laidback Ren, who is about to divorce his money-crazy wife, finds a time-traveling computer, he decides to use it to reboot his marriage.
Four comedians from Brazil riff on sexuality, politics, religion and motherhood – and set out to prove a woman's place is anywhere she wants it to be.
During an uprising in Russia's St. Petersburg, teen girl Lucky meets handsome Aditya, the Indian ambassador's son, and together they flee the chaos.
Needing a secluded place for a late-night tryst, two couples stow away in a mall after hours, but are quickly ensnared in a gruesome and deadly game.
This series dramatizes the life story of Mexican superstar singer Luis Miguel, who has captivated audiences in Latin America and beyond for decades.
In 17th-century Italy, a teenager learns about her destiny among a family of witches, just as her boyfriend's father hunts her down for witchcraft.
Pretending to marry in order to cohabitate, a small-town couple lands in endless awkward situations to hide the truth from their orthodox families.
With help from her magic toy chest, fun-loving Luna Petunia enters the fantastic land of Amazia, where adventures, friendship and learning await.
Luna Petunia returns to magical Amazia, adding memories to her scrapbook with old friends – and a new pal from the Animal Empire.
This mockumentary series follows the peculiar lives of six eccentric – and sometimes obscene – misfits who march to their own beat.
A bright and spirited seven-year-old girl uses her vivid, dreamlike imagination to navigate everyday adventures alongside her real and imaginary BFFs.
Haunted by disturbing visions, a workaholic takes a vacation with his family, but a detour leads them to an unsettling stranger and chilling events.
In the companion to 2013's "Bombay Talkies," four short films by four of India's biggest directors explore love, sex and relationships in modern India.

title_name: Lupin the 3rd: The Castle of Cagliostro: Special Edition
description: Lupin, his sidekick, Jigen, and the samurai warrior Goemon set out to take over an evil counterfeit operation at Count Cagliostro's fortress.
In this drama set in World War II-era Shanghai, a young actress gets caught up in a complex plot involving love, seduction and assassination.
Unabashed comedian Lynne Koplitz offers a woman's take on being crazy, the benefits of childlessness and the three things all men really want.
Three men from different nations must find their way out of the Amazon jungle – on foot – when they get lost on the way to Brazil's World Cup Final.
Fleeing London to evade a gangland debt collector, Omi Khurana returns to his native village in India, passing himself off as a successful lawyer.
The relationship between a journalist and a lawyer she meets while investigating a story grows complicated as she uncovers layers of deception.
On his first visit to his home city of Kolkata in 13 years, a Paris-based chef is faced with a cooking challenge that will change his life forever.

title_name: Mac & Devin Go to High School
description: Devin Overstreet may be the class valedictorian, but he hasn't had much life experience. Enter Mac Johnson, a 10th-year senior and weed dealer.
After relocating to a different town with her husband, a housewife begins to sense the existence of a mysterious presence in their new house.
A famous designer who's always pretended to be gay finds himself in crisis mode when threatened with exposure as the woman-chasing straight guy he is.
This collection cherry-picks trailers, forgotten scenes and poster art from 47 gory oldies, including Bay of Blood and The Blood Spattered Bride.
A stockbroker struggling with bipolar disorder goes to live with his estranged father in a cramped flat, where old resentments bubble to the surface.
A botched rescue strands Alex the lion and his companions in Africa. Sadly, Alex discovers he has little in common with the locals.
When a highly capable woman becomes secretary of state, she struggles to find balance between the demands of world politics and those of her family.
This documentary chronicles the rise of the footwear designer behind a billion-dollar empire and his subsequent comeback after a financial scandal.
After a trip to China, a struggling entrepreneur returns to India as the supplier of an illegal aphrodisiac — but all he ends up stimulating is chaos.
These Mexico City socialites may lead opulent lives, but a peek behind the curtain reveals a tangled web of intrigue, envy and personal struggles.
An Indian intelligence agent journeys to a war-torn coastal island to break a resolute rebel group and meets a passionate journalist.
The story of making "Lagaan," one of the millennium's seminal Indian films, is told from the point of view of production team member Satyajit Bhatkal.
Pregnant and overwhelmed, Diana hires a caretaker for her son with severe autism. But she soon begins to fear the new nanny has sinister intentions.
The Magi who became High King of the Seven Seas started as a boy determined to make the world a better place. He begins with a dangerous dungeon.
A land of mysterious ruins and a magical treasure hunt await young Aladdin and his courageous friend Alibaba for the adventure of their lives.
From baffling people on the street to orchestrating elaborate tricks, Justin Willman blends good-natured magic with grown-up laughs.
When an ordinary guy crosses paths 15 years later with his childhood sweetheart, now an actress, a magic cellphone allows him to be her protector.
Attracted to thrills across the globe, intrepid athletes venture to remote locations in pursuit of their extreme form of bliss.
An industrialist's daughter is forced to marry a rich heir by her greedy grandmother as her adopted sister bonds with the charismatic wedding planner.
From Argentina to Colombia, this stunning documentary follows five characters who share their deep connection to South America's majestic mountains.

title_name: Maharaja: The Story of Ranjit Singh
description: The tale of legendary warrior king Ranjit Singh, and his rise to establishing Punjab’s Sikh empire, comes to life in this animated feature.
A Punjabi man attempts to build a life in London in hopes of impressing his girlfriend’s mother, who insists her daughter marry a man outside of India.
Two young brothers encounter a singing bird who treats them to a musical reinterpretation of one of India’s most epic ancient tales.
In this comedy, characters from all walks of life go head-to-head around the mahjong table in a high-stakes contest of different playing styles.
To keep the boys in line, student council president Misaki runs the school with an iron fist – while secretly working as a waitress at a maid café.
A financially troubled Indian man heads to Singapore to find employment, while his pretty wife stays behind in a move that could cause trouble.

Major Ram Prasad Sharma yearns to see project Mission Milaap come to fruition and usher in an era of peace between two warring countries. But the evil Raghavan will do anything to stop the peace process.
An ordinary-looking guy weds the woman of his dreams, but his jealousy threatens to destroy their union in this lighthearted tale of marital mismatch.
After lying to his girlfriend, orthopedic surgeon Samir must conjure up a pretend wife in this musical comedy.
A successful writer returns to the town that launched his career, encountering people who spark nostalgic, often painfully illuminating flashbacks.
A woman with an entrepreneurial spirit takes life into her own hands by starting a beauty cream business that inspires other women to take chances.
Filmed over 10 years, this real-life thriller follows a DNA exoneree who, while exposing police corruption, becomes a suspect in a grisly new crime.
A look at the making of one of the first series to authentically portray and explore issues in a Hasidic community as they pertain to women's lives.
This "H2O" sequel follows Zac, a boy who accidentally turns into a merman and threatens the existence of three young mermaids who guard Mako Island.
After surviving a bomb attack, two low-level mobsters in Jerusalem change their ways and set about making strangers' Wailing Wall prayers come true.
With their relationship running on autopilot, a discontent husband and wife must confront their issues while on a trip with the extended family.
Class divides become thorns in the budding romance between the crony of a nativist Mumbai politician and the new, North Indian resident of his chawl.
Years after a police encounter separates him from his lover, an angry young man goes on a killing spree, with an equally vengeful cop on his heels.
An Argentine comedian espouses the values of feminism, speaking on topics like sex, language, abortion and why it's OK to let a man buy you dinner.
A brother-sister team who fake paranormal encounters for cash get more than they bargained for when a job at a haunted estate turns very, very real.
When a long list of shenanigans lands Tyler in hot water, he’s forced to suit up and spend his summer training for an elite junior lifeguard program.
On the heels of Junior Rescue training, Team Flounder returns to brave the beach in a series of thrilling saves and lighthearted laughs.
After receiving a strange present, a professor and his pregnant wife are plagued by tragedy and a paranormal presence that's determined to kill.
A self-trained engineer risks debt, love and reputation in his quest to improve the grueling work conditions of his mother and her weaving community.
A man undergoes a heart transplant following a serious injury and begins to take on some of the donor's motherly characteristics.
A childish idiot trapped in an adult's body, schoolteacher Dan hates his job, hates his girlfriend-less life and has good reason to fear his dad.
Mobeen is trying to be a good friend, follow the faith and raise his teenage sister. Yet his past – and everyday life – complicates matters.
In this kung fu tale set in Beijing, a young man armed with incomparable martial arts skills gets embroiled in the world of underground fight clubs.
Disguised as a bodyguard, a special agent must complete his national secret tasks while pandering to the whims of his ill-tempered world star.

title_name: Man vs Wild with Sunny Leone
description: The adventures of Bear Grylls get a unique spin as Bollywood star Sunny Leone hosts the show famous for revealing Bear's wilderness survival skills.
Forbidden love, fraying loyalties and flagrant hypocrisy emerge when sanctimonious politicians drive a madam’s brothel from the heart of Hyderabad.
With the assistance of a psychiatrist, an acclaimed filmmaker struggles to come to terms with a mysterious romantic trauma.
Concerned that dementia will soon steal his most cherished memories, a Hindu doctor hires a Mulsim rickshaw driver to take him to his childhood home.
A Chinese pharmaceutical lawyer framed for a vile crime teams up with a sharp-witted Japanese detective to stop a dangerous corporate plot.
Faced with few clues and an increasingly panicked public, the FBI calls on a new kind of profiler to help track down the infamous Unabomber.
A nondescript man in a mental hospital has an exciting life of adventure and romance – in his head. He may be insane, or maybe he's just having fun.
Two struggling strangers connect during a mind-bending pharmaceutical trial involving a doctor with mother issues and an emotionally complex computer.
While prepping for a family wedding, a young man falls for his sister’s friend, who has already been promised to someone else.
Under pressure to marry, a perennial bachelor hires a much younger woman to act as his fiancée, but her bond with his family throws his plan for a loop.
After getting fired, a police officer connects with a prostitute he met on the job in a red-light district and sets out to keep her off the streets.
The pleasant family life of an L.A. attorney is disrupted by the sudden arrival of his brother, who is obsessed with the Charles Manson murders.
The controversial and troubled Indo-Pakistani writer Saadat Hasan Manto finds his artistic choices challenged by censors.
Four stories by writer Sadaat Hasan Manto culminate in a single gruesome drama that's set during the partitioning of the Indian subcontinent.
An Indian business owner struggles to keep his company afloat amid global competition while trying to make up for lost time with his family.
The relationship between a painter and his admirer unfolds as an abstract, twist-filled hide-and-seek game against the backdrop of murder and revenge.
When caste discrimination prevents a villager from giving his deceased father a rightful burial, he takes his fight for equality to court.
A showbiz family revolving around its teen celebrity son desperately tries to hang on to fame and success in this savage satire of Hollywood.
In a town in southern Spain where racial tensions run high among the workers in its many greenhouses, a cop investigates the murder of a young woman.
When criminal psychologist Kate Fuller investigates a man who was seemingly murdered in his sleep by his wife, she uncovers a case like no other.
In this docuseries, soccer great Diego Maradona comes to Culiacán, the heart of the Sinaloa Cartel, to save the local team, the Dorados, and maybe himself, too.
Alternative comic Marc Maron is back on stage in New York to talk Chinese food, drug abuse, sex in hotel rooms and life with his girlfriend.
Marc Maron wades through a swamp of vitamin hustlers, evangelicals and grown male nerd children, culminating in a gleefully filthy end-times fantasy.
Battle-scarred stand-up comedian Marc Maron unleashes a storm of ideas about meditation, mortality, documentary films and our weird modern world.
Her marriage just ended and she's returning to work as a London detective after 12 years away. Is the serial killer she once investigated back, too?

title_name: March Comes in Like a Lion
description: Orphaned young, a reclusive 17-year-old professional shogi player starts to come out of his shell when three sisters take him under their wing.
A top-ranked college marching band’s members fight to keep their spots, memorize routines, tend to their social lives – and slay the competition.
Eclectic character comedian Marco Luque plays himself in this stand-up special about relationships, regional differences and his own love of movies.
Set in a world of greed, betrayal, sexual intrigue and rivalry, “Marco Polo” is based on the famed explorer’s adventures in Kublai Khan’s court.
A defiant warrior-monk arrives at Kublai Khan's court in chains and soon earns his tragic nickname in this 30-minute origin story.
An ex-assassin tries to leave her dark past behind until a power-hungry gang targets her and her family, forcing her to summon her killer instincts.
Maria Bamford performs a rapid-fire, playful stand-up set for crowds at park benches, bowling alleys and LA theaters in this roving comedy special.

title_name: Maria Bamford: The Special Special Special
description: Spend an evening with gleeful, oh-so-awkward Maria Bamford via her cozy, shot-at-home comedy special, which has a two-person audience: her parents.
Pop music superstar Mariah Carey hosts this all-star holiday celebration with special guests and a celebrity reading of "The Night Before Christmas."
Lured back to her hometown, a famous horror writer discovers that the evil spirit who plagues her dreams is now wreaking havoc in the real world.

title_name: Mariusz Kałamaga, Karol Kopiec, Wiolka Walaszczyk Hilarious Trio
description: Comedians Mariusz Kałamaga, Karol Kopiec and Wiolka Walaszczyk deliver an eclectic and energetic stand-up show at Klub Hybrydy in Warsaw.
After the friendliest divorce ever, a carefree but devoted father navigates post-split parenting life with his levelheaded ex-wife and two kids.
Rollicking, outrageous and audacious, Marlon Wayans gets raw on racism, age-appropriate rap rhymes, gay rights, raising kids and even the Kardashians.
When his wife goes missing, university professor Saurabh remains at home while the police investigate, but his grip on reality loosens as days pass.
After a young man charms the girl he loves into accepting his proposal, an accidental swap on their wedding day leads him to marry the wrong bride.
Academy Award-nominated filmmaker Noah Baumbach directs this incisive and compassionate look at a marriage coming apart and a family staying together.
Set up by experts, four couples meet at the altar for the first time and test their compatibility after the wedding.
Fact meets fiction in this docudrama chronicling the journey of a spacecraft crew as it embarks in 2033 on a mission to colonize the red planet.
The longtime mayor of Marseille is preparing to hand over the reins to his protégé when a sudden and ruthless battle erupts for control of the city.
In ancient China, Zhi Ming trains at the legendary Northern Shaolin temple to avenge the death of his father at the hands of a nefarious magistrate.

title_name: Martin Matte: La vie, la mort...eh la la..!
description: Quebecois comedy star Martin Matte serves up embarrassing personal stories, a solution for social media trolls and more in this unpredictable special.

title_name: Marvel & ESPN Films Present: 1 of 1: Genesis
description: This documentary explores the connections between elite athletes and Marvel superheroes such as Spider Man, Black Widow and Captain America.

title_name: Marvel Super Hero Adventures: Frost Fight!
description: In this Christmas-themed special, Captain America and the Avengers battle Loki and Ymir, who plot to steal Santa Claus' powers and conquer the world.
Agent Phil Coulson, seen in action in Marvel's The Avengers, assembles a team of top S.H.I.E.L.D. agents to investigate bizarre threats.
Blinded as a young boy, Matt Murdock fights injustice by day as a lawyer and by night as the Super Hero Daredevil in Hell's Kitchen, New York City.
On Halloween, the Hulk and Dr. Strange battle monsters wreaking havoc on New York and uncover an evil plot by Nightmare, ruler of the Dream Dimension.
Danny Rand resurfaces 15 years after being presumed dead. Now, with the power of the Iron Fist, he seeks to reclaim his past and fulfill his destiny.
A hoodie-wearing, unbreakable ex-con fights to clear his name and save his neighborhood. He wasn't looking for a fight, but the people need a hero.
Daredevil, Jessica Jones, Luke Cage and Iron Fist join forces to take on common enemies as a sinister conspiracy threatens New York City.
Haunted by a traumatic past, Jessica Jones uses her gifts as a private eye to find her tormentor before he can harm anyone else in Hell's Kitchen.
A former Marine out to punish the criminals responsible for his family's murder finds himself ensnared in a military conspiracy.
Ordinary girl Mary picks an extraordinary flower and travels to Endor College, a school for magic. But its foremost teachers have a sinister plan.
The daughter of a poor rice farmer overcomes the objections of her father and the demands of a male-dominated society to pursue a career in boxing.
In 1930s London, Michael Banks and his three children get some help turning their topsy-turvy world around when his magical childhood nanny reappears.
A young girl passionate about AI sets out to make an impact as three friends become crime-fighting superheroes. Based on the hit animated web series.
Eager contestants don big heads and furry suits to vie for the title of World's Best Mascot in this offbeat, comic romp from Christopher Guest.
Lively little Masha lives near the forest, where she has many wonderful adventures with her best friend, a bear who used to be in the circus.
Masha explains why there's no need to be scared of things like monsters, the dark, going to a new school, thunder and other common childhood fears.
Fairy tales get a funny twist when Masha retells them, because she tends to get the details just a little jumbled up in this animated kids' series.
Determined to make it in showbiz, an aspiring young actor considers turning his back on the beloved Irani café run by his family for generations.
A loving husband and father's joyful family life is rocked to its core upon the discovery that he has a young son borne from a past extramarital affair.
Dev tries to jump-start his acting career and elevate his dating game with help from his eclectic group of friends in this award-winning series.

title_name: Master Z: The Ip Man Legacy
description: In this spin-off, a martial arts expert once defeated by Ip Man is forced to abandon his reclusive lifestyle to combat a rising Chinese triad.
After living with a criminal father, two brothers on different paths head for a direct collision when an intriguing woman enters both of their lives.
A dutiful son must hide his pursuit of stand-up comedy from his staunch father, who expects him to inherit his store and uphold their Muslim beliefs.
A single man in his 30s overwhelmed by his domineering mother meets a lesbian couple willing to go to extreme lengths to have a child.
An unconventional police officer faces off against a gang of thugs as he tries to bring order to the far-flung village he’s been stationed in.

title_name: Mau Nieto: Viviendo sobrio… desde el bar
description: Performing at a bar, Mexican stand-up comedian Mau Nieto dishes on his modest upbringing, his failed relationships and his attempts to stay sober.
Comedian Maurício Meirelles explores his chaotic mind with scathingly funny views on family, prejudices, turtles and more in this stand-up special.
Hoping to find answers to her estranged father's mysterious illness, a young woman visits his old villa and uncovers a horrifying truth from the past.
A messaging app unites a mute prostitute, an unruly rich girl and a stormy young woman, three Hong Kong teens living in pain and excess.
A man's inability to conquer his personal insecurities and distrust of other people leads to problems with his on-again, off-again wife and their son.
A beautiful, wealthy woman’s insatiable appetite for romance leads to tragedy and a police investigation.
When a middle-aged divorcee returns to Kolkata to visit his ailing father, long-buried memories resurface, bringing new discoveries with them.
Mayday's Life Tour concert unfolds as five fading superheroes are summoned to save the world from an extraterrestrial enemy that detests sound.
Iranian American comic Maz Jobrani lights up the Kennedy Center with riffs on immigrant life in the Trump era, modern parenting pitfalls and more.
Hoping to pump up their sound, a punk band hires Pepe, a keyboardist with Down Syndrome, but tensions erupt when he steals the show with his talent.
Raw and outspoken, comedian Alexis de Anda bares her soul about weddings, exercise, sex, gynecologists, drugs and much more in this stand-up special.
Desperate to start a new life with his girlfriend, a teenage boy steals drug money from her father, who happens to be the town's corrupt lawman.
In New York's Little Italy, a low-level hoodlum wrestles with loyalty to his mobster uncle, his faith and his friendship with an inveterate gambler.
Steven Rinella scrounges in some of America's wildest terrains in this unscripted series showing him on the hunt for wild animals from ducks to deer.
Honoring service members whose courage merited the awarding of a Medal of Honor, this docudrama series re-creates their inspiring true stories.
Doctors Owen Maestro and Lola Spratt leave Childrens Hospital and join a secret arm of the CDC to investigate and destroy a deadly global virus.
After his father's murder, banking heir Cosimo Medici battles opponents of his artistic, economic and political visions for 15th-century Florence.
In 1930s Poland, a powerful psychic steers a group of strangers toward a fated convergence that ensures survival for one and annihilation for others.
In South London, tradition clashes with culture as a Nigerian father tries to instill his old-fashioned African values into his modern British family.
Created for the 50th anniversary of manga "Ashita No Joe," mechanized human fighters known as Megalo Boxers battle each other for boxing supremacy.
A professor mysteriously vanishes, leaving behind a host of suspects, a shadowy history and a clue: the anonymous birthday gift of a Bengali classic.

title_name: Meet the Trumps: From Immigrant to President
description: Learn about Donald Trump's family history, including his immigrant grandfather's gold-rush enterprises and his dad's development of a property empire.
After recovering from a tragic experience, a young woman makes a journey to her father's homeland and falls in love with a kind-hearted doctor.
In the early 1990s, the love between a cassette shop owner and a traveling circus performer challenges caste barriers and disapproving parents.

title_name: Melodies of Life - Born This Way
description: A celebrated pastry chef and his fellow staff members at a bake shop embark on bittersweet adventures in love, work and friendship.
When Melvin and his friends gather for dinner, their casual conversation takes a sharp turn as they begin to disclose raw truths about themselves.
While looking for the cryptic creator of an innovative augmented-reality game, an investment firm executive meets a woman who runs a hostel in Spain.
Glimpse into the brain's vast potential for memorization through the eyes of four competitive memory athletes as they share techniques and insights.
Male celebs play make-believe as high schoolers, welcoming star transfer students every week and engaging in battles of witty humor and slapstick.
A stranger to civilian life, a young Saudi farmer travels to Dubai, where he experiences a series of hilarious misadventures.
A year after his wife's death, a widower faces pressure from his Hasidic community to give up his son for adoption unless he finds a new partner.
Losing her memory – and her boyfriend – after a car accident, Jia-en crosses paths with a heart transplant recipient who helps her recall her past.
A hedonistic soccer mom takes a voyage of self-discovery when she tries to reconnect with her son by returning his pet rock to a Mediterranean island.

title_name: Merata: How Mum Decolonised the Screen
description: New Zealand film archivist Heperi Mita traces the cinematic legacy of his mother and trailblazing Maori filmmaker Merata Mita.
When he defies his cruel father and leaves New Caledonia to play rugby in France, young Soane learns hard lessons about life, love and success.
After rigorous testing in 1961, a small group of skilled female pilots are asked to step aside when only men are selected for spaceflight.
Two brothers clash with their half-siblings when a visit home to see their dying mother surfaces old secrets and becomes a fight for survival.
Fifteen years after a traumatic crime, a woman is released from psychiatric care and tries to drive out an evil spirit that continues to haunt her.
A simple auto-rickshaw driver on the streets of Lucknow, Hiralal Tiwari does everything he can to give his gravely ill daughter a happy life.
When his mother suffers a traumatic incident, a boy from the Mumbai slums treks to Delhi to deliver his written plea for justice to the Prime Minister.
In southern India, a laborer's dreams of owning a piece of land to farm is complicated by political corruption.
An unconventional high school philosophy teacher upsets a few parents and staff, romances others and inspires all his pupils, including his gay son.
This family-oriented retelling of the King Arthur legend finds Merlin arriving in Camelot, where he hones his magic skills with the help of his uncle.
A struggling LA musician tries to win over his new girlfriend's gruff dad and quirky, tight-knit siblings on a 10-day Christmas visit to Philadelphia.
To save a kidnapped loved one, a pack of wealthy men must return to their vigilante past when they are blackmailed to pull off a treacherous heist.

title_name: Merry Men: The Real Yoruba Demons
description: Four of the richest bachelors in Abuja, Nigeria enjoy a life of fast cars, palatial homes and female attention while concealing their true activities.
A detective arrests a doctor for crimes targeting medical professionals but later finds the real culprit in a tale of revenge, corruption and magic.
On a relentless quest to avenge his sister's murder, a man from Cape Town infiltrates a sprawling network of lowlifes and elites in Los Angeles.
A wary CIA officer investigates a charismatic man who sparks a spiritual movement and stirs political unrest. A fictional story not based on true events.
Dong Shancai is determined to excel at her dream university, where she encounters an elite clique of dashing, popular high-achievers – and finds love.
Disgusted by the gold-chain snatchers in his home city of Chennai, a man vows to combat the criminal menace by taking the law into his own hands.
Mysterious goons chase teenage slacker Angelino through chaotic Dark Meat City as he uncovers secret powers that could be the key to saving the world.
When street vices keep them coming back, three prisoners make sense of their lives in a penitentiary – and beyond it – through rap.
When a young soccer fan and his idol forge an unexpected friendship, the connection teaches them both lessons about life and their love of the game.
A sly art dealer tries to revive the career of his longtime pal, a surly painter, with a risky plan that tests their morals and friendship.
A mysterious gift from her late parents sends 12-year-old Mia into an enchanted world of elves, unicorns and an evil queen named Panthea.
When a terrorist escapes custody, MI-5 director Harry Pearce becomes the scapegoat. But the wily veteran still has some spycraft tricks up his sleeve.
After a dedicated cop accidentally kills a 12-year-old boy, he's fired, harassed and forced to take menial work as he tries to keep his life together.

title_name: Michael Bolton's Big, Sexy Valentine's Day Special
description: After Santa tells him he needs 75,000 new babies by Christmas to meet toy supply, Michael Bolton hosts a telethon to inspire the world to make love.
"SNL" star Michael Che takes on hot-button topics like inequality, homophobia and gentrification in this stand-up set filmed live in Brooklyn.
Benjie Nycum travels to Wyoming to visit his ex-lover, Michael Glatze, a former gay activist who now lives with his wife and works as a church pastor.
Comedian Michelle Wolf takes on outrage culture, massages, childbirth, feminism and much more (like otters) in a stand-up special from New York City.
An entrepreneur develops an adult entertainment online billing company – and winds up dealing with mobsters, the FBI, con men and terrorists.

title_name: Middle School: The Worst Years of My Life
description: At Hills Village Middle School, budding cartoonist Rafe and best pal Leo challenge their uptight principal by breaking every rule in his handbook.
Comedy duo Thomas Middleditch and Ben Schwartz turn small ideas into epically funny stories in this series of completely improvised comedy specials.
A scarred man operates a midnight diner in the backstreets of Shinjuku. No one knows his name or his story, but his customers each bring him theirs.
Patrons of an otherwise mundane Japanese diner find simple yet profound connections with one another based on the shared love of a particular dish.
In this talk show, comedian Mallika Dua serves up big laughs as Shalishka and whips up a meal with her celebrity pals who dish on their diets and lives.
An innocent toddler’s boundless curiosity – and extraordinary might – lead to mischief and adventure in his small Indian town.
From decorating his home to devouring sweets, join Bheem as he makes merry – and a bit of mischief – while the festival of lights is in full swing.

title_name: Mighty Little Bheem: Festival of Colors
description: From surprising stage performances to spraying colors with friends, join baby Bheem for all his Holi hijinks during the special spring festival.
Visitors arrive from space to help Red Ranger and his squad – temporarily stripped of their powers – fight against Lord Zedd and Rita Repulsa.
Five average teens are chosen by an intergalactic wizard to become the Power Rangers, who must use their new powers to fight the evil Rita Repulsa.
Mighty Raju preps for a new adventure in Rio de Janeiro, where he goes toe-to-toe with rival soccer players, faces capoeira fighters and more.
On this painfully honest but hilarious journey, Birbiglia struggles to find reason in an area where it may be impossible to find: love.

title_name: Mike Birbiglia: Thank God for Jokes
description: Comedian Mike Birbiglia takes the stage in Brooklyn and hits on hard truths about puppets, late people and the very real dangers of being funny.
Comedian Mike Birbiglia hits Broadway with a hilarious yet profound one-man show that recounts his emotional and physical journey to parenthood.

title_name: Mike Birbiglia: What I Should Have Said Was Nothing: Tales from My Secret Public Journal
description: Mike Birbiglia performs in this live concert special that features a riotous selection of the unique insights and observations culled from his diary.

title_name: Mike Epps: Don't Take It Personal
description: Mike Epps tears up the stage at L.A.'s historic Orpheum Theatre in a special packed with blistering impressions and unapologetically raunchy swagger.
In a raw stand-up comedy special, Mike Epps mixes it up as he tackles sexual misconduct, special ed, aging body parts and much more.
Politician and human rights campaigner Milada Horáková battles against all odds to defend her beliefs in a Czechoslovakia under Communist rule.
Years after his teen romance with Milea, a now-adult Dilan tells his version of their love story when a high school reunion brings them back together.
A group of millennials copes with the pressures of adulting by tackling a diverse set of problems from unemployment to cheating.

title_name: Miles Davis: Birth of the Cool
description: Unpack the mythology of Miles Davis and learn the true story of a jazz legend with never-before-seen footage and celebrity interviews.
When a cantankerous trainer mentors a persistent amateur boxer determined to go pro, deep-seated emotions become their strongest opponents.
Five beautiful but mysterious women move in with unsuccessful novelist Shin, who manages their odd household in exchange for a tidy monthly sum.
Next-gen restaurateurs get the chance to open their own pop-up eateries to impress the paying public – and a panel of discerning U.K. investors.
With the help of a cop, a psychologist and a woman who can foretell the future, a brilliant paralegal works to solve an array of perplexing mysteries.
Brilliant young students discover a breakthrough that could change humankind, but soon find themselves the subjects of a much bigger experiment.
When a twisted killer tells the police he'll only speak to a fictional 1980s TV detective, the washed-up actor who played him takes the gig.
In the late 1970s two FBI agents expand criminal science by delving into the psychology of murder and getting uneasily close to all-too-real monsters.
When a Marine's mission goes awry, he must survive behind enemy lines – without stepping off a mine – among the harsh elements of a desert war zone.
Take control of an adventure set in the Minecraft universe. The future of the world is at stake, and your decisions shape the story – so choose wisely!
A methane explosion leaves a group of miners trapped two miles deep into the earth with a small oxygen supply and desperate for any means of survival.
Mini-Wolf and his fun-loving pals friends are always on the look out for a new adventure – even if it includes a little bit of mischief.
Four animal superheroes called the Miniforce transform into robots to protect small and defenseless creatures from the hands of scheming villains.
Zenos wants to use the Earth’s negative energy for his own good – and it's up to Miniforce X to stop this space alien’s evil plans.

title_name: Minimalism: A Documentary About the Important Things
description: People dedicated to rejecting the American ideal that things bring happiness are interviewed in this documentary showing the virtues of less is more.
A nameless widow juggles multiple jobs to support her daughter’s decision to study abroad, only to discover that she has other plans.
In this game show hosted by Olympian Apolo Anton Ohno, contestants compete by completing 60-second challenges using common household items.
U.S. hockey coach Herb Brooks unites a motley crew of college athletes and turns them into a force to be reckoned with at the 1980 Winter Olympics.
Separated from his daughter, a father with an intellectual disability must prove his innocence when he is jailed for the death of a commander's child.
Unhappy after his new baby sister displaces him, four-year-old Kun begins meeting people and pets from his family's history in their unique house.
Viral video star Miranda Sings and her real-world alter ego Colleen Ballinger share the stage in a special packed with music, comedy and "magichinry."
This remake of the classic Grimm tale follows fair-skinned Snow White on a quest to regain her royal throne with help from a team of shady dwarves.

title_name: Miraculous: Tales of Ladybug & Cat Noir
description: When Paris is in peril, Marinette becomes Ladybug. Little does she know, her school crush Adrien is actually Cat Noir, another city-saving superhero.
Equipped with nothing more than a GED and strategies for the game of go, an office intern gets thrown into the cold reality of the corporate world.
Mistaking the sleeping passenger on his train for a drunk, a young man posts a picture of him online, unaware of his impulsive act's ugly repercussions.
After living in America for years, a teenage girl moves back to the Netherlands and is quickly singled out as a misfit by the popular clique at school.
When her boyfriend abruptly transfers schools, a gifted musician must pair up with an archrival to battle him in a student music competition.
In this revealing documentary, Taylor Swift embraces her role as a songwriter and performer — and as a woman harnessing the full power of her voice.
After ditching her domestic life to become a chef, a clueless maid crosses paths with two charming suitors who help her reach her dreams.
Herself a talented artist, O-Ei works with her father, Tetsuzo, later known as Hokusai, on the woodblock prints that would make Edo famous worldwide.
A quirk of fate sends an ordinary, sweet-natured high school girl and her father into the home of the school genius, on whom she has a huge crush.
The life of a radio talk-show host is turned upside down after a murderous caller dials into her program and asks her to choose his next victim.
On a summer night in 1890 Ireland, the unsettled daughter of aristocrats coaxes her father's valet to seduce her, though he's engaged to their cook.
When a gifted patissier with a gloomy past meets a bright and easygoing café owner, he begins to shed his thorns and learns to love again.
Explore how the mainstream media's often disparaging portrayals of women contribute to the under-representation of females in positions of leadership.
A space-time continuum glitch allows Vera to save a boy's life 25 years earlier, but results in the loss of her daughter, whom she fights to get back.
Determined to give her son a private school education, a single mother in the inner city uses all her resources to try to effect change in the system.
This documentary follows oceanographer Sylvia Earle's campaign to save the world's oceans from threats such as overfishing and toxic waste.

title_name: Mission Control: The Unsung Heroes of Apollo
description: Combining archive footage with present-day interviews, this documentary explores how Apollo's mission control helped change the course of history.

title_name: Mission Istaanbul: Darr Ke Aagey Jeet Hai
description: A television journalist makes a risky career move by accepting a job offer from a controversial Istanbul television station.
Resolving to get married soon, hardworking Si-yi finds love in an unexpected place, but her ex and her job interfere with her plans.
Two strangers meet by chance on a trip to Thailand and form a connection when they realize their former romantic partners ended up getting together.
As Hitler's Nazis threaten to take command of Britain's skies, a squadron of Polish pilots arrives to aid the Royal Air Force against a mutual enemy.
A gambler mired in debt thinks another cardsharp may just be his good luck charm as the two head for New Orleans to buy into a high-stakes poker game.
The real Mitt Romney is revealed in this documentary that goes beyond the sound bites with unprecedented access to his 2012 presidential campaign.
Arab-American comedian Mo Amer recounts his life as a refugee comic, from traveling with the name Mohammed to his long path to citizenship.
Comedian Mo Gilligan blends smooth moves and sharp humor as he riffs on humble beginnings, family dynamics and the complex art of dancing in the club.
There's an organization gathering espers for a nefarious purpose. Powerful psychic Mob, however, is just trying to be the protagonist of his own life.
When Banagher Links meets the mysterious Audrey Burne, he inherits the Unicorn Gundam and is swept up into the battle for space colony independence.
On a terraformed post-disaster Mars, a group of child security agents rebel against the adults who betrayed them and the oppressive Earth government.

title_name: Modest Heroes: Ponoc Short Films Theatre
description: Two underwater siblings surviving on their own. A boy with a serious egg allergy. A man invisible to the rest of society. Three short animated tales.
A courageous villager moves to the ancient city of Mohenjo Daro, where he falls for the daughter of a priest and does battle with a tyrant.
A lethal game of cat and mouse stretches from the desert to Tinseltown after Hollywood bad boy Thomas runs afoul of a cunning and dangerous drifter.
A young boy's life shifts when he's sent to work at a mechanic's shop far from his suburban home until an opportunity forces him to make a tough choice.
An imaginative, big-hearted bunny and his friend, a shy chick, explore the everyday joys of their pastel-colored world.
Former Olympian Molly Bloom ran a high-stakes poker game for the stars – until her lofty lifestyle nearly sent her to prison.
After her stepdaughter is sexually assaulted at a party, a furious mother sets out to destroy the lives of the four perpetrators who walked away free.
Two fierce mothers become rivals when a school contest forces their kids, both model students, to compete against one another to be the best in class.
After 20 years, Ana María returns to Mexico and vies for control of her family's tequila empire as it threatens to crumble under corruption and secrets.
Two corporate spies with a $5 million haul for selling secrets are held hostage by a thief, triggering a game of cat and mouse to gain the upper hand.
A documentary on why and how "Money Heist" sparked a wave of enthusiasm around the world for a lovable group of thieves and their professor.
When his daughter and son-in-law fall prey to a scam, Istanbul con man Asım Noyan meets his match in a madcap kingpin of an underground gambling world.
Jin and his dragon monster Draka set out on a racing adventure and try to save the kingdom from evil forces.
Inspired by Khon dance drama and Thai martial arts, a fighter scarred by the past joins forces with a determined cop to battle an organized crime ring.
A talking monkey famous for his TV commercials dreams of breaking into real movies. But first he stumbles upon a brother and sister who need his help.
Seeking revenge on his employer, a lazy bank agent and his two dim-witted friends concoct an elaborate but flawed heist.
A family’s festive Halloween plans take a spooky turn when an evil witch's curse transforms the costumed clan into actual monsters.
Clawdeen wants to turn an abandoned power station into a salon for monsters and "normies" alike. But Moanica's got a shocking plan to ruin everything.
At a Monster High party, Lagoona and pals are sucked into the reef, where she'll have to come to terms with her flaws and confront an old frenemy.

title_name: Monster High: New Ghoul at School
description: Insecure new student Frankie Stein struggles to fit in at Monster High, where ultra-cool ghoul Cleo De Nile and hunky monster Deuce rule the roost.
When a teenager discovers he's not really human, he ventures out to a remote island to explore his roots and confronts a series of wild challenges.
Max, Lily and Goo love to put their minds together and use their math skills to overcome any obstacle, even ones with two left feet or ten thumbs.
An American platoon stationed in the Middle East is thrust into battle with a breed of tentacled aliens whose rapid spread threatens human survival.
Art imitates life when Chiyo discovers her crush is a famous artist who wants to use their budding relationship as inspiration for his romantic manga.
Prominent comedians pay tribute to Monty Python's best work in this five-part series, along with selected clips of sketches.
Follow the evolution of the British sketch comedy troupe that redefined humor and shaped an entire generation of American comics.

title_name: Monty Python Live (Mostly): One Down, Five to Go
description: Live from London in a sold-out final show, surviving members of the British comedy troupe reprise old roles and break out in irreverent song and dance.

title_name: Monty Python: Before the Flying Circus
description: Discover how six seemingly ordinary but supremely talented men became Monty Python, sketch comedy's revolutionary comedy troupe.
The members of Monty Python reunite on stage to talk about making their iconic show that changed sketch comedy forever.

title_name: Monty Python: Live at The Hollywood Bowl
description: Film clips and Terry Gilliam animations feature in this live-to-tape performance of greatest hits, including "Travel Agent" and "Solo Wrestling."
The legacy of comedy group Monty Python, whose irreverent brand of humor has tickled the ribs of millions, is explored in this documentary.
The Pythons elevate the absurd to new heights and bring their sketches to German TV, working in phonetic German, at times with an Australian accent.
